  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        
        <div xml:id="Aink2">
            <lg type="edition">
<l>              vāḻi yātaṉ vāḻi yaviṉi</l>
<l>              viḷaika vayalē varuka viravala</l>
<l>              reṉavēṭ ṭōḷē yāyē yāmē</l>
<l>              pallitaḻ nīlamoṭu neyta ṉikarkkun</l>
<l>              taṇṭuṟai yūraṉ kēṇmai	</l>
<l>              vaḻivaḻic ciṟakka veṉavēṭ ṭēmē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>              “May Ātaṉ prosper, may Aviṉi prosper.</l>
<l>              let the paddy fields ripen, let the beggars come”</l>
<l>              thus wants our mother. We,</l>
<l>              “the intimacy with the man from the village by the cool ghat,</l>
<l>              where waterlilies rival with many-petalled lotuses,</l>
<l>              let it grow step by step,” thus we want.</l>
              
            </lg>
        </div>
